    indications: ['Essential hypertension (not for initial therapy)', 'Heart failure with reduced ejection fraction post-MI', 'Cardiovascular risk reduction in high-risk patients ≥55 years', 'Diabetic nephropathy with hypertension', 'Post-STEMI and NSTEMI cardiovascular protection', 'Chronic kidney disease with proteinuria', 'Hypertension with volume overload', 'Left ventricular dysfunction prevention'],
    contraindications: ['Hypersensitivity to ramipril, hydrochlorothiazide, sulfonamides, or any component', 'History of angioedema related to ACE inhibitor therapy', 'Pregnancy (all trimesters) - FDA Boxed Warning', 'Anuria (inability to produce urine)', 'Bilateral renal artery stenosis or single kidney with renal artery stenosis', 'Concomitant use with aliskiren in diabetic patients', 'Severe hepatic impairment', 'Hypersensitivity to sulfonamide-derived drugs'],
    warnings: ['Angioedema: Life-threatening airway obstruction - higher risk in Black patients and those with previous angioedema', 'Fetal toxicity: FDA Boxed Warning - Discontinue immediately if pregnancy detected', 'Hyperkalemia: Monitor serum potassium, especially with renal impairment or diabetes', 'Hypotension: Particularly in volume-depleted patients, heart failure, or elderly', 'Renal function deterioration: Monitor creatinine and BUN', 'Hepatic necrosis: Rare but potentially fatal', 'Neutropenia/agranulocytosis: Monitor CBC in patients with renal impairment or collagen vascular disease', 'Electrolyte imbalances: Hyponatremia, hypokalemia, hyperuricemia', 'Acute angle-closure glaucoma and myopia', 'Photosensitivity reactions', 'Systemic lupus erythematosus activation'],
    sideEffects: ['Common (>2%): Dry cough (5-10%), dizziness (4%), fatigue (3%), headache (2%)', 'Cardiovascular: Hypotension, chest pain, palpitations, syncope', 'Respiratory: Persistent dry cough (most common ACE inhibitor side effect)', 'Gastrointestinal: Nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, abdominal pain', 'Metabolic: Hyperkalemia (4% with ramipril alone, 2% with combination), hyperuricemia, hyperglycemia, hyponatremia', 'Neurological: Headache, dizziness, fatigue, weakness, paresthesia', 'Dermatologic: Photosensitivity, rash, angioedema', 'Musculoskeletal: Back pain, muscle cramps', 'Genitourinary: Polyuria, nocturia, impotence', 'Rare but serious: Angioedema (0.1-0.2%), severe hypotension, acute renal failure, hepatic necrosis, neutropenia, thrombocytopenia'],
    interactions: ['Potassium supplements/salt substitutes: Risk of hyperkalemia - monitor serum potassium', 'Lithium: Increased lithium levels and toxicity - monitor lithium concentrations', 'NSAIDs (ibuprofen, naproxen): Reduced antihypertensive effect, increased nephrotoxicity risk', 'Aliskiren: Contraindicated in diabetic patients - risk of hyperkalemia, hypotension, renal dysfunction', 'Antidiabetic agents: HCTZ may increase blood glucose - monitor and adjust diabetes medications', 'Digitalis glycosides: Hypokalemia increases digitalis toxicity', 'Cholestyramine/colestipol: Reduced HCTZ absorption - separate administration by 4-6 hours', 'Gold salts: Increased risk of nitritoid reactions', 'Alcohol/barbiturates: Enhanced orthostatic hypotension', 'Corticosteroids: Intensified electrolyte depletion'],
